parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission's reverse gear can cause the vehicle to be unable to reverse, leading to safety risks, inconvenience, and potential accidents.
symptoms: Delay in engaging reverse gear
reverse gear fails to engage
reverse gear engages intermittently
complete failure of reverse gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the valve body can cause transmission problems, including delayed or failed engagement of reverse gear, leading to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: Delay in engaging reverse gear
reverse gear fails to engage
reverse gear engages intermittently
complete failure of reverse gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall without warning, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls without warning
the fuel pump makes a loud whining or grinding noise
the fuel pump fails to prime
the vehicle has difficulty starting
the vehicle has a rough idle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel tank leak can cause gasoline to spill onto the ground, creating a fire hazard and potentially causing explosions or fires.
symptoms: Gasoline leaks from the tank
the tank is wet with gasoline
the garage or surrounding area is filled with gasoline vapor
the vehicle has a strong gasoline smell.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning seat heater can cause a burning smell, potentially leading to a fire or burns to the driver or passengers.
symptoms: Burning smell when the seat heater is turned on
visible signs of burn or scorching on the seat leather or fabric.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty seat heater element can overheat, causing a burning smell, potentially leading to a fire or burns to the driver or passengers.
symptoms: Burning smell when the seat heater is turned on
visible signs of burn or scorching on the seat leather or fabric
excessive heat emanating from the seat.
